# Lis Pendens (Notice of Pending Action)

Drafts a recordable notice that provides constructive notice of pending litigation affecting title or right to possession.

## Prerequisites

1. **Jurisdiction + county recorder** — state, county, and local recorder formatting rules.
2. **Filed pleading** — complaint or amended complaint that asserts a qualifying real property claim.
3. **Case metadata** — court name, division, case number, filing date, party names.
4. **Property records** — current deed/title report with full legal description and APN/tax ID.

## Output Structure / Process

**A. Intake Table (must be complete before drafting)**

| Field | Value | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| State + County |  |  |
| Court (full name) |  |  |
| Division/Dept |  |  |
| Case Number |  |  |
| Filing Date |  |  |
| Plaintiff(s) (exact) |  |  |
| Defendant(s) (exact) |  |  |
| Property Address |  |  |
| Legal Description |  |  |
| APN / Tax ID |  |  |
| Recorder Formatting Rules |  |  |
| Service Requirements |  |  |

**B. Statute/Rule Mapping (fill, then cite in document)**

| Topic | Requirement | Citation |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Statutory authority |  | [VERIFY] |
| Real property claim definition |  | [VERIFY] |
| Mandatory warning language |  | [VERIFY] |
| Verification format |  | [VERIFY] |
| Attorney certification |  | [VERIFY] |
| Service timing/method |  | [VERIFY] |
| Recorder formatting |  | [VERIFY] |

**C. Drafting Checklist**

- [ ] Caption matches court’s required format.
- [ ] Parties listed exactly as in operative complaint.
- [ ] Case number and filing date accurate.
- [ ] Property description includes legal description + APN.
- [ ] If multiple parcels, each parcel has its own legal description + APN.
- [ ] Real property claim summary ties relief directly to title/possession.
- [ ] Statutory authority cited.
- [ ] Mandatory warning language included verbatim.
- [ ] Verification/declaration completed and correctly signed.
- [ ] Attorney certification included if required.
- [ ] Proof of service prepared if required.

**D. Document Template (adapt to local format)**

```text
[Recording Requested By:]
[When Recorded Mail To:]
[Space for Recorder’s Stamp per county rules]

Attorney Name (Bar No.)
Law Firm
Address
Phone | Email | Fax (if required)
Attorney for [Plaintiff/Party]

[COURT CAPTION EXACTLY AS FILED]

NOTICE OF PENDING ACTION (LIS PENDENS)

1. Parties. [Plaintiff(s)] filed this action against [Defendant(s)].
2. Court and Case. This action is pending in the [Court], Case No. [###], filed on [Date].
3. Property.
   a. Street Address: [Address]
   b. Legal Description: [Full legal description]
   c. APN/Tax ID: [APN]
4. Real Property Claim. The action includes claims for [quiet title / specific performance / foreclosure / partition / lien enforcement / other], which affect title to or right to possession of the Property.
5. Relief Affecting Property. Plaintiff seeks [specific performance / decree quieting title / foreclosure sale / partition / other property-related relief].
6. Statutory Authority. This Notice is recorded pursuant to [State statute citation] [VERIFY].
7. Mandatory Notice. [Insert exact statutory warning language if required] [VERIFY].

Dated: [Date]                    __________________________
                                 [Attorney Name]
                                 Attorney for [Party]

VERIFICATION / DECLARATION
I, [Name], declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of [State] that I have read the foregoing Notice of Pending Action and the facts stated in it are true and correct of my own knowledge, except as to matters stated on information and belief, and as to those matters I believe them to be true.

Executed on [Date] at [City, State].
__________________________
[Signature]
[Printed Name]
[Title/Capacity]

[ATTORNEY CERTIFICATION (if required)]
I certify that I have reviewed the operative complaint and that the real property claim has probable validity under [statute] [VERIFY].
__________________________
[Attorney Signature]

[PROOF OF SERVICE (if required)]
I served the Notice of Pending Action on the parties as follows: [method, date, address/service list].
__________________________
[Server Signature]
```

**E. Attorney Attention Notes (include as short addendum)**

- Missing source data: [list].
- Statutes/rules not verified: [list with [VERIFY]].
- Potential issues: [e.g., non‑qualifying claim, inadequate property description, service deadline risk].
- Recorder-specific formatting risks: [list].

## Guidelines

- Verify real property claim qualifies under controlling statute; do not record for purely monetary or unrelated claims.
- Use deed/title report language verbatim for legal description; street address alone is insufficient.
- Match party names and case number exactly to the operative complaint.
- Insert statutory warnings verbatim where required; mark uncertain text with `[VERIFY]`.
- Confirm county recorder margins, font size, and stamp-space rules before finalizing.
- Ensure service is completed within statutory timeframes; include proof of service when required.
- Flag any jurisdiction-specific expungement standards or probable validity requirements.
